text: Kekere Moukailou (; born 8 August 1992) is an Ivorian professional footballer who plays as a defender for Myanmar club Hantharwady United. . He has played in Thailand.http://www.supersubthailand.com/news/12873-6/index.html#sthash.yqyQ85B7.iCl7uh0e.dpbs ==Club Career== Under contract with Myanmar's Yadanarbon from 2015 to 2016, Moukailou was teammates with Myanmar national team members Zaw Linn Tun, Sithu Aung, Ye Ko Oo, and Aung Thu. On playing football in Myanmar, the Ivorian defender stated that the climate was harmful to health and it could potentially cause heart disease. Was mistaken for fellow Ivorian Djawa Maximin in a 2015 league match and was given a second yellow card when Maximin was given the first. His contract with Yangon United was renewed for another year just before the 2018 Myanmar National League.http://www.ygnutd.com/index.php?pid=3&id;=918&&news;=article&⟨=eng ==References== Category:1992 births Category:Living people Category:Ivorian footballers Category:Yangon United F.C. players Category:Association football midfielders Category:Expatriate footballers in Myanmar category:Myanmar National League players Category:Expatriate footballers in Thailand Category:Ivorian expatriate footballers
